
[1]thyme

   THYME, n. usually pronounced improperly time. [L. thymus.]

   A plant of the genus Thymus. The garden thyme is a warm pungent
   aromatic,much used to give a relish to seasonings and soups.

   Thymus. [Gr.] In anatomy, a glandular body, divided into lobes,
   situated behind the sternum in the duplicature of the mediastinum. It
   is largest in the fetus, diminishes after birth, and in adults often
   entirely disappears. It has no excretory duct, and its use is unknown.
   In calves it is called sweetbread.
